  "title": "Automated Bounties & Quests",
  "summary": "Automated bounties, a unified developer dashboard, and a massive reshuffle of the model routing layer.\n\nWe built a fully automated workflow for Community Quests. You can now claim bountied issues, ship the code, and automatically receive Pollen credits when your PR merges. We tied the idempotency keys to immutable GitHub IDs, so you'll still get paid even if you change your username mid-quest.\n\nThe developer portal got a serious overhaul. We unified the design system so navigating your keys and models is actually a visually consistent experience. More importantly, we added an Earnings dashboard so developers can track the Pollen generated by their apps, and wired up Stripe Customer Portal for auto top-ups so your API access doesn't randomly halt when you sleep.\n\nA lot of models moved around this week to keep things fast and cheap. We added GPT-5.4-mini, Mistral 4, and ElevenLabs Flash v2.5. DeepSeek V4 Flash was moved to OpenRouter and is now completely free. We also re-routed Qwen Vision and OpenAI embeddings to bypass rate limits, and wired up the gateway so LTX-2 can now handle image-to-video generation.\n\nWe stopped lying about 500 errors. Upstream user-input errors (like malformed multipart requests) now correctly return a 400 Bad Request. We also fixed the image generation endpoints to surface the actual upstream failure reasons instead of returning an empty JSON object, so you can actually debug your broken prompts.",
